 children — including her son Lewis Polk Rutherfurd, the Hong Kong venture capitalist — plus ten grandchildren and twelve great-grandchildren at her death. White roses were placed on her casket at the Church of the Heavenly Rest in New York."}],"slug":"alice-rutherfurd-1917"},"HD5055":{"id":"HD5055","has_descendants_documented":false,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":true,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"generation_from_thomas":9,"is_easter_egg":false},"parents":{"father_id":"HD2601","mother_id":"X01884"},"tags":["physician","yale_graduate"],"sources":[],"marriages":[],"gender":"male","number_of_marriages":0,"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"birth":{"year":1875,"month":5,"day":6,"city":"Demopolis","county":"Marengo County","state":"Alabama","country":"USA"},"death":{"year":1904,"month":3,"day":29,"city":"New York","county":"New York County","state":"New York","country":"USA","age":28,"cause":"acute pneumonia developed within hours of becoming chilled while performing an autopsy"},"cross_connections":[],"bio":{"display_name":"Dr. John Metcalfe Polk","first_name":"John","last_name":"Polk","middle_name":"Metcalfe","married_names":[],"title":"Dr."},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"burial":{"place":"Woodlawn Cemetery","city":"Bronx","state":"New York"},"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"death","header":"Died at twenty-eight from autopsy-acquired pneumonia","body":"John Metcalfe Polk caught a chill while performing an autopsy in March 1904. Acute pneumonia developed within hours, and he died on March 29, 1904 at age 28. He had been an Instructor in Medicine and Physical Diagnosis at Cornell Medical College — the institution his father William Mecklenburg Polk had served as Dean — for just over a year."},{"number":2,"category":"career","header":"Cornell Medical Instructor; researched influenza blood changes","body":"After Cornell Medical School MD 1899 and Bellevue internship, John Metcalfe Polk studied pathology in Vienna in 1902. He joined Cornell Medical College as Instructor in Medicine and Physical Diagnosis in January 1903. His research focused on blood changes produced by infectious diseases, particularly influenza and influenza-associated pneumonias — work that was 'making observations of much value' at the time of his death."},{"number":3,"category":"family","header":"Namesake of his nephew John Metcalfe Polk, 1908-1948","body":"Four years after his death, his elder brother Frank Lyon Polk and Elizabeth Sturgis Potter named their first son John Metcalfe Polk (HD5048, 1908-1948) in his honor. The name passed directly from uncle to nephew within the same Hooker generation. Both men are buried at Woodlawn Cemetery in the Bronx."}],"slug":"john-polk-1875"},"HD5057":{"id":"HD5057","has_descendants_documented":false,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":true,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"generation_from_thomas":9,"is_easter_egg":false},"parents":{"father_id":"HD2601","mother_id":"X01884"},"tags":["died_in_infancy"],"sources":[],"marriages":[],"gender":"female","number_of_marriages":0,"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"birth":{"year":1877},"death":{"year":1878},"cross_connections":[],"bio":{"display_name":"Serena Devereux Polk","first_name":"Serena","last_name":"Polk","middle_name":"Devereux","married_names":[]},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"serena-polk-1877"},"HD5058":{"id":"HD5058","has_descendants_documented":false,"classification":{"include_in_path_cal